Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped) into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large, wide-bottomed ovenproof pan on medium heat.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an ovenproof dish before baking.

Once hot, add the @sliced mushrooms{120%g} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Transfer the mushrooms to a #bowl{} and set aside.

Pop your (now empty) pan back on medium-high heat and add the onion and @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until the onion has softened and the lardons are browned, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Stir in the @diced British chicken breast{1%pack}, cooked mushrooms and garlic, then cook until the garlic is fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook lardons thoroughly.

Stir the @risotto rice{175%g} into the pan and cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the @boiled water{600%ml}(for the risotto), @mixed herbs{1%sachet} and the @chicken stock paste{20%g}. Stir well to combine.

Bring back up to the boil, then pop a #lid{} on the pan (or cover with #foil{}). Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the water has been absorbed, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Rocket Salad ==

Meanwhile, zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}.

In a large bowl, combine a squeeze of lemon juice with the @sugar{1%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp}(for the dressing). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Just before serving, add the @wild rocket{40%g}, then toss to coat in the dressing.

== To Serve ==

When the risotto's ready, remove from the oven. Stir in a knob of butter (if you have any) and three quarters of the @hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated).

> TIP: Add a splash of water to loosen the risotto if needed.

Stir in a pinch of lemon zest and squeeze in some lemon juice. Taste and add more salt, pepper or lemon zest and juice if needed.

Serve your chicken, bacon and mushroom risotto topped with the rocket salad and remaining cheese. Enjoy!